Beryl Sprinkel, Chairman ofPresident Reagan's Council of Economic Advisors, denouncedprotectionism as a means of addressing the U.S.s' mountingtrade imbalance and said stepped-up ecomonic growth would be amore effective means of reducing the deficit.    "Rather than risking the outbreak of protectionism weshould strive to reduce trade restrictions and to promote amore open system of international trade," Sprinkel said.    Sprinkel, in a speech delivered to the Los Angeles Chamberof Commerce, also said the budget deficit must be reducedthrough lower government spending in order to promote growth. Reuter&#3;